IHello Vernon,
Trust you're doing great and hope this email finds you well.
Yes, I am interested in funding your company but just so you know here are criteria for me to invest in this beautiful idea/project of yours.
I look for high-quality entrepreneurs with good performance - either individual, or the company's specific industry or prior entrepreneurial ventures and look at your passion and commitment to the new business idea, and your ability to inspire confidence as We would be working together as partners, I as the investor.
Team credibility is essential. In addition, you must be open to and comfortable with receiving input provided by me, you must demonstrate a strategy to improve, there are plenty of great business ideas.
Funds must be used to accelerate your plans. I look for individuals and companies that can grow quickly and manage the scale necessary to succeed.  and you must demonstrate a plan to generate significant profits beyond the initial product idea. Do you have a strategy to achieve multiple sources of revenue?
I require well-conceived financial projections, based on sound assumptions, demonstrating consistent profits and cash flow growth.
I invest in first-of-a-kind new ideas, and common products and services. Any breakthrough innovation must be accompanied by a strong business plan,  I am interested in the strategy you select, but more importantly in the how - the operational strategy that shows specific steps you will take to achieve.
I look for high-quality entrepreneurs with good performance to demonstrate a strategy to improve in what I will be investing in.
Get back to me if you deem it fit that you have such qualities with your executive summary/ business plan.
Best Regards,
Dr. Safarik Zdenek
